    "The IAA scores for the annotation revision results, all approaching 0.99, indicate that the discussions among annotators during the review meeting phase were effective, leading to meaningful consensus and agreement.",
    "Baseline evaluation.",
    "The goal of this evaluation wasn't to achieve optimal performance, but rather to establish a baseline for future comparisons and demonstrate the usefulness of the TFDR corpus.",
    "In this study, we employed five distinct language models to fine-tune and evaluate their performance on the downstream tasks of NER, KSR and RE using TFDR corpus.",
    "The TFDR corpus was split into two distinct datasets: a training set consisting of 590 abstracts (79.7%) and a testing set containing 150 abstracts (20.3%), making a total of 740 abstracts."
